<paragraph id="C9CC5195D4C63C845DD5C98B7FA5D7EE" pageNumber="732">
Etymology Gr 
<taxonomicName id="154ECCDFC264D6167FC4D3E61A196B8A" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pidax Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pidax Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="732" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pidax">pidax</taxonomicName>
, fountain, referring to the spray-like pattern of the cephalic carinulae.
</paragraph>
